getEigenAgent(address).details: Gets the ERC-6551 EigenAgent account of the user.

params.user: owner of the EigenAgentOwner NFT that controls the ERC-6551 EigenAgent account.

getEigenAgentOwnerTokenId(address).details: Gets the tokenId of the EigenAgentOwner NFT owned by the user. Owner of the NFT controls the associated 6551v EigenAgent account.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.newEigenAgentOwner721: address of the eigenAgentOwner712 NFT contract.

spawnEigenAgentOnlyOwner(address).details: Spawns a ERC-6551 EigenAgent for a user.

params.user: address to mint a EigenAgentOwner721 NFT and create a ERC-6551 EigenAgent account for.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

tryGetEigenAgentOrSpawn(address).details: Tries to get a user's 6551 EigenAgent account if they have one, or spawns a new EigenAgent for the user if they do not already have one. Mind the gas costs is higher if they need to mint.

params.user: address to retrive (or spawn) their ERC-6551 EigenAgent account.

updateEigenAgentOwnerTokenId(address,add.details: This callback is triggered every time a EigenAgentOwner721 NFT is transferred.

params.from: the account where NFT is being transferred from
params.to: the account where NFT is being transferred to
